MPs were yesterday told a Swiss company behind the Sh17.7 billion tender to make digitised stamps for KRA allegedly used fraud to land the lucrative contract.Public Procurement Oversight Authority director general Maurice Juma told the Public Investments Committee that SICPA Security Solutions SA Ltd could be held accountable for fraud if it was awarded the contract before being registered locally.Kenya Revenue Authority awarded the Excise Goods Management System tender for production of 12 billion digitised stamps to SICPA Ltd in 2010.